Andrew Golding, chief executive of property giant Pam Golding Properties, has shared some of the finest properties currently in the group’s portfolio including a 4 bedroom house in Constantia, priced at R59 million, and a 5 bedroom home for sale in Sandhurst, Johannesburg. for R65 million. Both suburbs feature among the most expensive in the country, with a home in Sandhurst averaging R15.7 million, and R12.2 million in Constantia Upper. The Sandhurst property is architecturally designed by Jeremy Williams “to create a unique blend of modern which encompasses light, sky and nature”. It sits on over 8,600 sqm of land. The house includes  a quadruple reception entrance hall with windowscapes of light, sweeping glass staircase, indoor/ outdoor water features, stone walls, private elevator- sets the tone for a home designed for grand entertaining yet comfortable family living. It includes five free flowing reception areas, consisting of formal lounge, dining room, informal lounge, relaxation room/media, room all leading to an entertainers patio, wooden deck and centrally located, elevated rim flow infinity pool. A third level consists of five separate bedroom suites each with own dressing rooms and en suite bathrooms opening to balconies and views, while a ground level  has garaging for at least 10 cars and a separate room allowing for options/ numerous uses including a man cave, movie theatre etc. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-360482" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/5-bed-Sandhurst-1.png" alt="" width="1060" height="638" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/5-bed-Sandhurst-1.png 1060w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/5-bed-Sandhurst-1-300x181.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/5-bed-Sandhurst-1-1024x616.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/5-bed-Sandhurst-1-768x462.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85