ur set in the secluded Silverhurst Estate, Upper Constantia. Nestled in the Cape’s most prestigious residential estate, lies this magnificent family home. Set in an elevated enclave of the gracious Silverhurst Estate, this extremely well secured, exclusive private property enjoys unimpeded views of the surrounding mountain peaks. “Designed on a grand scale by renowned architect Michael Dall, the stately entrance lives in perfect symmetry with the arched Palladian windows, intent on creating a warm and welcoming presence. “The triple volume entrance hall graciously receives you and you are instinctively drawn to the view beyond. As you pause and take in the surroundings, you realise that this is a place where you are invited to live your best life,” Pam Golding said. As you move from the formal sitting room, through to the fully fitted bar, and on to the country style kitchen and family room, you finally reach a spacious entertainment lounge. Triple glazed stack back doors open out to a covered verandah overlooking the garden, landscaped by Francesca Watson, as well as the swimming pool. A second working kitchen, temperature-controlled wine cellar, study, gym and guest en suite are also located on the ground floor. Reaffirming the owners’ impeccable sense of design, the interiors come to life with imported wallpaper accents, French Oak wood flooring, bespoke light fittings and custom-made cornices, architraves and skirtings. A sweeping staircase ushers you up to the luxurious master suite, two spacious bedrooms and your own private and exclusive sound-proof cinema room with state-of-the art surround sound. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-360474" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/4-bed-Silverhurst-0.png" alt="" width="1101" height="703" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/4-bed-Silverhurst-0.png 1101w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/4-bed-Silverhurst-0-300x192.png 300w,